New Records: New Zealand claimed their first win against Australia in Australia in any format since 2011.
Key Match Events: Devon Conway scored 92 runs off 58 balls with seven fours and two sixes.
Finn Allen struck 42 off just 16 balls.
Mitchell Santner and Tim Southee both took three wickets each.
David Warner fell for three in the second over.
Phillips pulled off one of the catches of the tournament to remove Stoinis for seven.
Tim David was out for 11, becoming Santner's third wicket.
Post-Match Reflections: Devon Conway expressed pride in the team's performance and credited Finn Allen for providing momentum.
Conway mentioned that victory over Australia on any occasion is significant for New Zealand.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The match was a repeat of the 2021 final in Dubai where Australia won.
Australia's next match is against Sri Lanka in Perth, while New Zealand will face Afghanistan in Melbourne.
